<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>About Us - FixMyHome</title>
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Grotesk:wght@400;500;700&family=Source+Sans+3:wght@400;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css" />
  <%- include('partials/favicon-head') %>
</head>
<body class="site-body auth-body">
  <div class="auth-theme-toggle">
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-theme-toggle>Dark mode</button>
  </div>
  <main class="auth-shell legal-shell">
    <section class="auth-hero">
      <p class="eyebrow">About FixMyHome</p>
      <h1>Built to make local home help easier to trust and easier to hire.</h1>
      <p>FixMyHome helps homeowners post real jobs, compare clear bids, and stay organized from the first message through payment, review, and support.</p>
      <ul class="auth-highlights">
        <li>Homeowners can describe work clearly and attract better bids</li>
        <li>Handymen get a cleaner workflow for quoting, messaging, and winning jobs</li>
        <li>Admins have the tools to keep trust, billing, and support moving smoothly</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="auth-card app-card legal-card">
      <h2>What we care about</h2>
      <p>We want FixMyHome to feel transparent, local, and dependable. That means clearer bids, safer payments, stronger moderation, and less confusion for both sides of the job.</p>

      <h2>Who it is for</h2>
      <p>FixMyHome is for homeowners who need trusted help around the house and handymen who want a more organized way to discover work, communicate clearly, and get paid with confidence.</p>

      <h2>How we support users</h2>
      <p>From password recovery to billing support and dispute handling, we’re building the product around practical support workflows instead of leaving users stuck when something goes wrong.</p>

      <h2>Questions?</h2>
      <p>You can reach our team through the <a href="/contact">Contact Us form</a>.</p>
    </section>
  </main>
  <%- include('partials/site-footer') %>
  <script src="/theme-toggle.js" defer></script>
</body>
</html>
